'From Squeak3.1alpha of 28 February 2001 [latest update: #4108] on 26 June 2001 at 3:48:48 pm'!"Change Set:		booleanPhraseFix-swDate:			26 June 2001Author:			Scott WallaceFixes the bug that generated wrong code when a test-pane coercion to a boolean took place."!!CategoryViewer methodsFor: 'support' stamp: 'sw 6/26/2001 15:45'!booleanPhraseForRetrieverOfType: retrieverType retrieverOp: retrieverOp player: aPlayer	"Answer a boolean-valued phrase derived from a retriever (e.g. 'car's heading'); this is in order to assure that tiles laid down in a TEST area will indeed produce a boolean result"	| outerPhrase getterPhrase receiverTile  rel finalTile |	rel _ (retrieverType == #number)		ifTrue:		[#<]		ifFalse:		[#=].	outerPhrase _ PhraseTileMorph new setOperator: rel type: #boolean rcvrType: retrieverType argType: retrieverType.	getterPhrase _  PhraseTileMorph new setOperator: retrieverOp type: retrieverType rcvrType: #player.	getterPhrase submorphs last setSlotRefOperator: retrieverOp.	getterPhrase submorphs first changeTableLayout.	receiverTile _ aPlayer tileToRefer bePossessive.	receiverTile position: getterPhrase firstSubmorph position.	getterPhrase firstSubmorph addMorph: receiverTile.	outerPhrase firstSubmorph addMorph: getterPhrase.	finalTile _ aPlayer tileForArgType: retrieverType.	"comes with arrows"	outerPhrase submorphs last addMorph: finalTile.	outerPhrase submorphs second submorphs last setBalloonText: (ScriptingSystem helpStringForOperator: rel).    	^ outerPhrase! !!Utilities class methodsFor: 'fetching updates' stamp: 'sw 6/26/2001 15:48'!readNextUpdatesFromDisk: n	"Read the updates up through the current highest-update-number plus n.  Thus, 	Utilities readNextUpdatesFromDisk: 7will read the next seven updates from disk"	self applyUpdatesFromDiskToUpdateNumber: ChangeSorter highestNumberedChangeSet + n		stopIfGap: false! !